    "The corrected lensfit measurement variances ОҪ вҖІОө,i are then used to define a corrected shape measurement weight per source w вҖІ i using a modified version of Eq.",
    "( 18):w вҖІ i = пЈ® пЈҜ пЈҜ пЈҜ пЈҜ пЈҜ пЈ° ОҪ вҖІ Оө,i Оө 2 max 2Оө 2 max -4ОҪ вҖІ Оө,i + ОҪ Оө,pop пЈ№ пЈә пЈә пЈә пЈә пЈә пЈ» -1.",
    "(23) Ellipticity correctionThe final step in our recalibration process is the correction of source ellipticities, designed to remove any residual PSF leakage into the distribution of measured shapes.",
    "This process is similarly performed in bins of resolution and S/N, but also in bins of photo-z (which are used for cosmic shear tomography).",
    "As such, this process formally does not contribute to the sample statistics calculated here, as the choice of tomographic bins for KiDS-Legacy is decided during the cosmological analysis."
